cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.RO, cs.CV, cs.SY

The paper discusses deep reinforcement learning and its application in autonomous driving. The most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), as the paper proposes a new approach for policy gradient descent. The second likely sub-category is cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), as the paper discusses the lack of generalization capability in deep reinforcement learning and proposes a solution. The third likely sub-category is cs.RO (Robotics), as the paper applies the proposed approach to the 3D autonomous driving environment TORCS. The fourth likely sub-category is cs.CV (Computer Vision), as the paper may involve image processing and analysis in the autonomous driving application. The fifth likely sub-category is cs.SY (Systems and Control), as the paper may involve control theory in the autonomous driving application.
